==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''xanthine'''
#{{chemistry}} any of a group of [[alkaloid]]s, that include [[caffeine]], [[theophylline]], and [[theobromine]] as well as the [[parent compound]], a precursor of [[uric acid]] found in many organs of the body

===Usage notes===
*There is much confusion between this word and [[xanthein]], and they are often interchanged.

